<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-B5C11BED-C928-4685-96AE-0B0949CC35A9" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-B5C11BED-C928-4685-96AE-0B0949CC35A9" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">19 Print and wind with a locked tension bar</title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-94560935-D638-4480-81D4-A4514A7B3B52"><p class="- topic/p ">Winding media with a locked tension bar is only used for stiff media, in order to prevent media transportation issues. 
</p></abstract><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Functional description</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><prereq id="GUID-8A380DA4-9A3D-4942-A1E4-3FDCFD6532DB" class="- topic/section task/prereq "><ul id="UL_B5A4DF99AE1444DAADEEEFA23632434A" class="- topic/ul "><li id="LI_8C5090D1B0A9491991ADAE1605968F69" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The use of the tension bar is set in the media type configuration in the RIP software. For winding with a locked tension bar, you must select <uicontrol translate="no" class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">locked tension bar</uicontrol> under <ph translate="no" class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">Winding tension</uicontrol></ph>. 
</p></li><li id="LI_7EDD718158EF4A1E980DD19CC7D8A2DC" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you have placed a take-up roll core on the roll winder. 
</p></li><li id="LI_FA6B064B40BC48B4A1CE90BDAAE240C5" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Make sure you have tape ready. 
</p></li><li id="LI_14DD23BAF724443EA4DB7F8A3CE88E2D" class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer is ready to print. 
</p></li></ul><note type="important" id="GUID-B07EB767-62B4-4139-AD78-3FF7FD651E4C" class="- topic/note "><p class="- topic/p ">Use the emergency stop button, to stop the winder immediately. Do not forget to switch it on again. 
</p><fig id="FIG_B11CBF6A9C474BD38861D943E4EBB54B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-675D0A0B-D259-48EB-9C75-AE9FF6D4CA34-low.png" id="IMAGE_570CF1E0790B41349B5028C76604B797" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-675D0A0B-D259-48EB-9C75-AE9FF6D4CA34-low.png"/></fig></note></prereq><steps id="GUID-B6C56BB2-C545-4D36-AC18-AD302A9C580F" class="- topic/ol task/steps "><step id="STEP_6DC11A1C61FA40B1BE34D52CC7EE3CF3" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel tap on the <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Output</text></uicontrol></ph> icon. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_2BF18C6C01B44B1C810A0B5D06861661" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make sure <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Wind the output</text></uicontrol></ph> is set to <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Yes</text></uicontrol></ph>. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_2145034036F540BABDFDD2E9B3A069CE" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-228855AB-307C-4AB9-9ACF-4F2B9D48FD36-low.png" id="IMAGE_4F94CAAE8315487F9AB61DAB76F2F262" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-228855AB-307C-4AB9-9ACF-4F2B9D48FD36-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_B426224AACCF48EBB10CFBE2BC7B0228" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd "> Start a print job. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer spools the media until it reaches the tape position. The clamp closes and the operator panel gives a message indicating you can tape the media. 
</p></info></step><step id="STEP_FB773BD273684E6B813C5A9F96885DE0" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Make sure the media guides are out of the way as they can damage the media. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "/><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_3E11EB6A0BCE44A197DF6B1716BE8C27" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-205B7A15-97F3-4CEE-8427-BC73FA41E6AD-low.png" id="IMAGE_2296EF9D63C046658DF5430A74E36896" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-205B7A15-97F3-4CEE-8427-BC73FA41E6AD-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_15FCA6666E9744668C1B29FE5ABB8742" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Take the leading edge of the media and align it on the core. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_8B8DBF9365A444AF9AE3AAA16B4B6AAE" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Tape first the center and then the sides of the media to the core. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_73B8E56281454379BB035428C4C5184D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-898064C1-D114-4FBB-848C-40381A1A5144-low.png" id="IMAGE_CA9B52F062F348AA956DF0A5C2176B0F" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-898064C1-D114-4FBB-848C-40381A1A5144-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_4FEF6F41C9DF4C9CAE8EE11F2320F9B8" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Place the tension bar lever in locked position. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_B3EA2277B83049B2841977E6DB3E4CD2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-0C96A077-2A8C-47CE-8AB9-3A51AF962F21-low.png" id="IMAGE_3581895483454509860FD28D63208D13" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-0C96A077-2A8C-47CE-8AB9-3A51AF962F21-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_ED335C5343934497BC271D9A946473DC" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Lift up the tension bar and place it correctly on top of the media. 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><fig id="FIG_206A421587CB47308C117FE6961377D8" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-B609AAFE-B291-4047-AA4C-1D155E2F6EF8-low.png" id="IMAGE_667686CE32AC45D9BCFE762C397618DF" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-B609AAFE-B291-4047-AA4C-1D155E2F6EF8-low.png"/></fig></info></step><step id="STEP_4E812DA9922F45F888C6E6D1F6D91FDB" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">On the operator panel tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Ready</text></uicontrol>.</ph>. 
</cmd></step><step id="STEP_4B8AB57AFD144E77B012EC302DFAE020" class="- topic/li task/step "><cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Move the media guides towards the middle to align with the media. Tap on <ph class="- topic/ph "><uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "><text class="- topic/text ">Ready</text></uicontrol>.</ph> 
</cmd><info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info "><p class="- topic/p ">The printer starts printing while winding the job. Make sure the tension bar falls into the locked position. 
</p><fig id="FIG_1FEA2C18B489454CBAA88D6F596F93E7" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7C43EBFF-C34F-4271-9FD7-61096DA17498-low.png" id="IMAGE_E213C03679E1468987518ECFD7D2359F" keyref="" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7C43EBFF-C34F-4271-9FD7-61096DA17498-low.png"/></fig></info></step></steps><postreq id="GUID-0C5BCD5B-64CE-423B-B285-499ACD9AB600" class="- topic/section task/postreq "><p class="- topic/p ">When you want to stop winding you have to cut the media. 
</p></postreq></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-77E3E148-DF16-4838-9432-CE905B393B0C.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Functional description</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
